message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Ecuador in the past 100 years is the 7.8 magnitude earthquake that struck the country on April 16, 2016. This earthquake, known as the 2016 Ecuador earthquake, caused widespread devastation and was one of the deadliest earthquakes in Ecuador's history. The quake resulted in the loss of 671 lives, injured thousands, and caused extensive damage to infrastructure, homes, and public services. The event had a profound impact on the country's economy and prompted a massive international humanitarian response.
